text: {| |} The Morane-Saulnier S,also known as MoS-10, was a large twin-engined biplane bomber designed and built in France around 1916. Powered by two Renault 12E V-12 water-cooled piston engines, with Hazet type side radiators, the 'S' was given the STAé designation MoS-10 and serial MS-625.Davilla, 1997, p.327 ==Variants== ;Morane-Saulnier S: company designation for Renault 12E V-12 powered version ;MoS.10 B.3:official French government STAe designation for the S ;Morane-Saulnier Y: company designation for Hispano-Suiza 8Aa V-8 powered version. ;MoS.24 B.3:official French government STAe designation for the Y ==Specifications (S) == ==References== ===Citations=== ===Bibliography=== * * ==External links== * Category:1910s French bomber aircraft S
